free: #e A child had a frog and raised a dog at home.
#c 一個小孩,有青蛙,在家養了一隻狗。
#e He always took them to bed (when) they slept.
#c 他總是帶他們到床上當他們睡覺時。
#e It was late in the evening.
#e The child came here to sleep.
#e His dog slept with him on his bed.
#e The frog he put inside the container came out.
#c 他放在罐子裡的青蛙出來了。
#e When he was not aware of it.
#e (When he woke up,) it was sunrise.
#e He got up and looked at the jar.
#e The dog that slept (with him) got up too.
#c 跟他一起睡的狗也起來了。
#e (They) looked for the frog in the jar.
#e The dog went to smell the inside of the jar to look for the frog.
#c 狗去聞罐子裡的味道,要去找青蛙。
#e The child looked for the frog inside his shoes but did not find it.
#c 小孩在他的鞋子裡找青蛙,可是沒找到。
#n 老師覺得應該是 isahiza: there.
#e This dog stuck in the jar.
#e The child by the window saw the dog fell with the jar.
#c 在窗戶旁的(小孩)看到狗跟罐子掉下去了。
#e (Then) they went out to look for the frog.
#c 他們就去外面找那個青蛙。
#e (They) went to the mountain and saw this beehive.
#e They did not know what that was.
#e This bird went to play at the beehive.
#e The child saw on the ground and found ...
#e (He) saw this (something) came out. (It) was not the frog.
#c 他看到這個出來,不是青蛙。
#e The dog went to shake the tree...the beehive there.
#c 這個狗去搖樹...那裡的蜂窩。
#e The hive fell on the ground.
#e This (hive) fell down (because of) the dog.
#c 這個蜂窩因為狗掉下來。
#e The child climbed up the tree and called inside the hole.
#c 小孩爬上樹,往洞裡面叫。
#e (He) called the frog's name toward the inside of the tree.
#e (He) called but it was not a frog that came out. (He) saw an owl come out.
#c (他)叫了,可是不是青蛙跑出來,(他)看到貓頭鷹出來。
#e The owl came out. (The boy) got frightened.
#c 貓頭鷹跑出來,(他)嚇到了。
#e (The boy) fell on the ground from up the tree.
#e It seems that there is nothing that can be done.
#e The beehive that fell down, (the bees) chased the dog.
#c 蜂窩掉下來,(蜂)追那個狗。
#e The owl chased the child and (the child) hid on top of the rock.
#c 貓頭鷹追那個小孩,小孩藏在石頭上。
#e The child was holding a branch.
#e He grabbed on to some branch.
#n 老師覺得講不清楚的地方應為下面的句子:
#n Note: Informant feels the inaudible portion should be the sentence below:
#e The dog on the rock was hiding from the bee.
#e What is that branch that he was grabbing on to?
#e The child hung on to the (deer's) antlers.
#e (The deer) took (the child) to the cliff.
#e The dog also fell into the river. Both of them.
#c 狗也掉進河裡.他們兩個。
#e The deer chased them, and tossed them (into the water).
#c 鹿追他們,把他們丟到水裡。
#n 老師覺得講不清楚的地方應為sapok: af.hit.
#n Note: Informant feels the inaudible portion must be 'sapok' (af.hit).
#e (The child) and the dog stood up.
#e The dog, wide-eyed, sat on the child's shoulders.
#c 狗,張大眼睛,坐在小孩的肩膀上。
#e They heard the sound of a frog (croaking) from (the other side of) a piece of wood.
#e at the back of the tree.
#e There were two frogs at the back of the tree.
#e He took (the frog) in his hand.
#c 他們把他的青蛙帶回家。
#e The dog was very happy too.
#e He went home through the river.
